The Metamorphoses, written in the dactylic‚ or heroic, verse and almost an heroic poem in matter as well as in torm, comprising about twelve thousand lines in fifteen books, is his most extensive and most important work. It is the great storehouse in the Latin language of Greek myth and legend. The ancients, intimate with nature and wondering at her mysteries‚ often felt that man or god was concealed beneath her visible appearance. Ovid gathers together the marvelous stories ot the changes of man or god to other forms and, combining with thern the accounts oi natural phenomena and poetic legend, forms one continuous song from the creation of the world to the change ol Julius Caesar to a star.
